Londen Jan Kent & comp
sence my last of 19 curs recd. yours of 30. 27 & 32 post
god send the goods from the nord well to arrive, hopeing
mij 5 packes there will come in time for this convoj for
Rottm the 5 p clothes are to law price, I must have fen
of non under 5 p rouw, with pray observe for the futture
& lett the 3 packs you ordered 19 curs bee 6 p of 5 Æ’ clothes
6 of 4 p without single do zins assorted as I ordered 12 Jan
in patt, & 19 curs that is 3 grayes & one white gray & 2
draps 5Æ’ clothes 4 grayes on the white grayes, &on darck
drap, or the like browne modecollour 4 p cloth you say
brayes & kersyes will resen, there by yoit ordered you to
buy 100 p there under 30 a 40 tof sta Henry wood
or a1 the rest of the best standfield, or the like or such
as are best peunj worth, & now upon yd opinion of riseng
soo desire you to buy 150 p that is 50 more then ordered
last & one pack of whitte baeys more of 12 p. 60 Æ’ or
there about he avie goods 12 ditto or 33 a 54 st & the
rest of the pack of labout 40 all to be sent to hull
to be shipped for Amstm or Rott the first convoy
that shall come butt which before no ship too goods bill
till convoy are there & when I have the patt of the ordered
clothes from thence & that you advise mee to be time
to buy cloth best salall send more instruction a governo
as for good from london I must blame you & am vere
angrej you should omitt shipping as I order, if you have excut
to have neglected last convoy for Rottm you have non to
excuse the negleett for Amst, which convoj arrived last week
examin my orders beeng alwayes to ship for anney of them places
when you have to send mee spe clothes & there in you have been
backwad then 3 yeare, & though you had spa clothes to ship
yett neare sended anney for & Amst & such thinghs are a
great preiudice to mee & I can not so fowards by haveing
all my spa clothes in one convoy, & thebe by forved bo gett
en sured where by each convoy ventured sometthing I can
have my goods with case & often something: & this I
write you, & writt you all allong, & yett you go your way
which if you will continue must oblige mee to beke othen
meahites, I have p your bill of MÂ£ 200 & inclises
bills: boath, for ste Â£300 on fintzel & harris on prs
the neodfull & pas to my acct N.2 in the pack N.2 is
to red

23 feb
dermonde Joris Bleegh
Ick hebbe in langen d'eere niet gehadt ue te vernemen, ick hope, dat
ick ue niet hebbe geoffenseert, want ue noyt 6 maenden gelyck nu hebb
achter gebleven daerentusschen hope ick dat gij met den vasten al eenigh goet
sult noodigh hebben, ue biddende dat gij mij wilt comen besoecken &
den ouden knecht om den nieuwen ooch niet en wiltrlaeten, gebruycke
de vrijscheyt hier beneffens ue eene quittantie te seynden van vijstigh
guldens, tot las te destadt dermonde, gelijck ue voor mij voor desen
noch wel hebt besorght, hope dit oock sult effectueren, & ue over
commende mij sult comen besoecken, waer naer verlange t blijv
